[{"id":"VH908213","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"&nbsp;The figure presents 4 circles. Circle 1 is labeled “L i with a positive one charge.” Circle 2 is the same size as Circle 1 and is labeled “M g with a positive 2 charge.” Circle 3 is larger than Circles 1 and 2, and is labeled “N a with a positive one charge.” Circle 4 is the same size as Circle 3 and is labeled “C a with a positive 2 charge.”\" height=\"97\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH908213.g01.png\" width=\"400\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The diagram above represents four cations, all shown to the same scale. Which cation would be predicted by Coulomb’s law to have the strongest ion-dipole attraction to water, and why?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH908213_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L i with a positive one charge\"><math alttext=\"L i with a positive one charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Li</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because it is the smallest group 1 metal ion.</p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M g with a positive 2 charge\"><math alttext=\"M g with a positive 2 charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Mg</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because it has the largest charge-to-size ratio.</p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a with a positive one charge\"><math alttext=\"N a with a positive one charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Na</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because it has the smallest charge-to-size ratio.</p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C a with a positive 2 charge\"><math alttext=\"C a with a positive 2 charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Ca</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because it is the largest group 2 metal ion.</p>\n"],"answer":1}]